<bibRefCitation author="Huang, C. M." box="[974,1118,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" refId="ref7426" refString="Huang, C. M. (1981) Orthoptera: Acrididae, Catantopinae, Pyrgomorphinae, Oedipodinae. In: Insects of Xizang. Vol. 1. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 69 - 71." type="book" year="1981">Huang, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with a single male specimen from Medog County (alt. 
<quantity box="[447,607,186,213]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6199999999999999" metricValueMax="2.15" metricValueMin="1.09" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" unit="m" value="1620.0" valueMax="2150.0" valueMin="1090.0">1090–2150 m</quantity>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[628,712,186,212]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[725,796,186,212]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">China</collectingCountry>
. Then, it was transferred to genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uvarov" authorityYear="1942" box="[1192,1321,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Assamacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1321,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">Assamacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Yin in 1984. 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, H. C. &amp; Xia, K. L." box="[221,403,222,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" refId="ref7555" refString="Li, H. C. &amp; Xia, K. L. (2006) Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Vol. 43. Orthoptera, Acridoidea, Catantopidae). Science Press, Beijing, 724 pp." type="book" year="2006">Li &amp; Xia (2006)</bibRefCitation>
figured the head (in anterior view) of 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang, 1981" authorityName="Huang" authorityYear="1981" box="[831,976,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Tenuifemurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curticerca">
<emphasis box="[831,976,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">A. curticerca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In this paper, 
<specimenCount box="[1142,1267,222,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
collected from the 
<typeStatus box="[192,240,258,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<date box="[364,508,258,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" value="2003-08">August 2003</date>
are believed to be conspecific with the male based on external features, and should be regarded as topotypes. The female is similar to the female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang, 1981" authorityName="Huang" authorityYear="1981" box="[880,1031,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Tenuifemurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicerca">
<emphasis box="[880,1031,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">A. longicerca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but different from it by: 1) each of 9 
<superScript attach="none" box="[165,178,329,343]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">th</superScript>
–11 
<superScript attach="left" box="[219,232,329,343]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">th</superScript>
antennal segments 4.5 times as long as wide (3 times in the latter), 2) mesosternal interspace 1.4 times as wide as long (as wide as long in the latter), 3) tegmina reaching the middle of 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1027,1041,365,379]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">rd</superScript>
abdominal tergite (not reaching the posterior margin of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[388,404,401,415]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="548">nd</superScript>
abdominal tergite in the latter). Here, its female was described for the first time.
